			| 1. You are going to read a magazine article about "Feng Shui". Here is the first part of the article.
		p
			center
				table(cellpadding='3', cellspacing='2', width='600', bgcolor='#ffbc90')
					tr
						td
							b
								| Making a House into a Home
								p
									| This month's House and Home looks at Feng Shui, the 3000 year-old Chinese art of living harmoniously in our homes.
							p
								| Have you ever gone into a neighbor's house and felt immediately "at home"?
								| Or you walk into an office or building and feel uncomfortable, but you don't know why.
								| You could be experiencing the effects of Feng Shui.
								p
									| The Chinese believe all things contain energy. Feng Shui, meaning "wind and water", is the art of organizing buildings
									| to use this energy positively. It can have an effect on our homes, relationships and work, too.
									| Use our guide to improve your homeand life!
									p
			p
				b 2. Choose the best answer to the questions below. 
				p
					ol
						li
							| What is Feng Shui?
							p
								input(type='radio', name='q2a', value='1', checked='checked')
								| a technique to help you feel comfortable in buildings and offices.
								br
								input(type='radio', name='q2a', value='2')
								| the art of organizing well the places we live and work in.
								p
									li
										| How does Feng Shui work?
										p
											input(type='radio', name='q2b', value='1', checked='checked')
											| by using air and water in a special way.
											br
											input(type='radio', name='q2b', value='2')
											| by using correctly the natural energy in all objects and places.
											p
					center
						button.eval(data-target='t1') Check answers
	form#t2
		p
			b
				| 3. Now look at the rest of the article. Choose the title for each section of the article.
			p
				ol
					li
						select(name='q3a')
							option(value='x')
								| Choose Title
								option(value='1')
									| Bedroom
									option(value='2')
										| Kitchen
										option(value='3')
											| Bathroom
											option(value='4')
												| Living room
						br
						| This room contains two conflicting elementsfire and water. Because of this, the stove and the sink shouldn't be close together.
						| Don't put the stove in a corner or in front of a large window. Ideally, the stove also won't be across from the door.
						| The room should be rectangular or squareirregular shapes have a negative effect on the flow of energy.
						| A spacious room with good light is perfect.
						p
							li
								select(name='q3b')
									option(value='x')
										| Choose Title
										option(value='1')
											| Bedroom
											option(value='2')
												| Kitchen
												option(value='3')
													| Bathroom
													option(value='4')
														| Living room
								br
								| Don't put objects that reflect across from the bedthis includes mirrors and televisions.
								| The bed shouldn't face the doorput it diagonally opposite.
								| If you live in a house on two floors this room shouldn't be above the garage or the kitchen.
								| Don't put any plants here. Don't put the bed next to a window or your spirit might leave the house while you're asleep!
								p
									li
										select(name='q3c')
											option(value='x')
												| Choose Title
												option(value='1')
													| Bedroom
													option(value='2')
														| Kitchen
														option(value='3')
															| Bathroom
															option(value='4')
																| Living room
										br
